  program: sem-tool
  args:
    - validate
    - "--help"
---
success: true
exit_code: 0
----- stdout -----
Simply validates an argument, to confirm it is a valid Semantic Version

The Status Code will be 0 if it is valid, non-zero if it is not.

Usage: sem-tool validate [OPTIONS] <VERSION>

Arguments:
  <VERSION>
          Version to validate

Options:
  -s, --small
          "Small" will ensure the MAJOR, MINOR & PATCH components are under [u64::MAX]

      --mcp
          Run an MCP server over stdio that exposes this CLI's clap schema

      --mcp-http <ADDR>
          Run an MCP server over Streamable HTTP at ADDR (e.g. 127.0.0.1:8080)

      --export-skills <DIR>
          Generate Agent Skills (SKILL.md) from tools, resources, and prompts, then exit

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

----- stderr -----
